  "market_context": "ES on the hourly chart around Thu 26 Dec '24, price expanded out of a consolidation, ran the prior low, and printed a bullish closure back inside — a reversal candle around the 50% of the previous daily candle, suggesting bullish continuation.",
  "key_observation": "Initial hourly reversal swing low is too wide to give 2R targeting the highs, so the analyst drops to the aligned 5-minute timeframe and uses T-spot (0.5 of the down-close series) and a fair value gap as continuation entry POIs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the ES 1H, identify a consolidation followed by expansion and check if a reversal forms around/above 50% of the previous daily candle.",
    "Step 2: Confirm the hourly reversal — price sweeps the prior low and prints an aggressive bullish close (expansion met with expansion).",
    "Step 3: Wait for a closure through the series of down-close candles on the hourly to validate a protected swing low.",
    "Step 4: Reject entering off the hourly swing low directly because stop placement on the low into the highs does not yield 2R.",
    "Step 5: Drop to the 5-minute (aligned with the hourly) where price shows aggressive move down and aggressive move back up into the failure-swing highs as target.",
    "Step 6: With no FVG and no formed higher low yet, mark 0.5 of the down-close candles (T-spot) as the POI for a continuation entry.",
    "Step 7: Price retraces into the T-spot, closes over the down-close series — take continuation long, stop under the low, target the highs for ~2R.",
    "Step 8: For a missed first entry, use the 5-minute fair value gap as a better POI; price taps the FVG, closes through the down-close candles into it, giving ~3.17R vs 2.38R.",
    "Step 9: Track each subsequent protected swing (FVG tap + closure through down-close candle) higher until the objective at the highs is hit.",
    "Step 10: Stop seeking new entries once the objective is reached — a new phase of price only begins at highs/lows where reversals can form."
  ],
  "outcome": "Continuation longs delivered approximately 2.38R on the T-spot entry and 3.17R on the FVG entry, with price tracking higher through multiple protected swings until the high target was taken.",
  "lessons": "When the HTF reversal swing is too wide for 2R, drop to the aligned LTF and use T-spot or FVG as continuation POIs. Track protected swings higher with closures through down-close candles until the objective is hit, then stop entering.",
